We'll split the 4.3% rate by 12 since the rate is annual and the periodic payment is monthly. Hence we will express the rate in the following equation:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Rate} &= \dfrac{0.043}{\text{12}}
\end{aligned}$$

Now, let's calculate the remaining balance of the loan after eight years using the present value annuity computation.

$$ \begin{aligned}
PVA &=\$1,113.46\times\dfrac{1-\dfrac{1}{\left(1+\dfrac{0.043}{12}\right)^{264}}}{\dfrac{0.043}{12}}
\\[20pt]
&=\$1,113.46\times\dfrac{ 0.6111}{0.003583333}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{\$189,874.10}
\end{aligned}$$

As can be seen in our computation, the remaining balance due after eight years, if the APR is 4.30%, is $189,874.10.

Parallel to the first computation, for the reason that the periodic payment is monthly, we will split the 4.05% rate by 12 because the APR is an annual rate. Hence, we will express the rate with the equation as follows:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Rate} &= \dfrac{0.0405}{\text{12}}
\end{aligned}$$

Let's now calculate the combined value of the present value of the loan at 4.05% and the present value of the loan's remaining balance after eight years.

$$ \begin{aligned}
PVA &=\$1,113.46\times\dfrac{1-\dfrac{1}{\left(1+\dfrac{0.0405}{12}\right)^{96}}}{\dfrac{0.0405}{12}}+\dfrac{\$189,874.10}{\left(1+\dfrac{0.0405}{12}\right)^{96}}
\\[15pt]
&=\$1,113.46\times\dfrac{ 0.2764 }{0.003375
}+\dfrac{\$189,874.10}{1.381893247}
\\[10pt]
&= \$ 91,173.50+\$ 137,401.42 
\\[5pt]
&= \boxed{\$228,574.92}
\end{aligned}$$

Based on our calculation, the combined present value of the loan at 4.05%, and the remaining balance after eight-year is $228,574.92.

Next, subtract the combined values from our previous calculation to the loan amount to determine the amount to be discounted. The following formula will be used:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Amount Discounted} &=\text{PV of loan and balance after eight years}-\text{Loan amount}
\end{aligned}$$
